      <akn:section eId="sec_28:2_610">
        <akn:num>28:2-610</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Anticipatory repudiation.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2-610_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>for a commercially reasonable time await performance by the repudiating party; or</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2-610_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>resort to any remedy for breach (section 28:2-703 or section 28:2-711), even though he has notified the repudiating party that he would await the latter’s performance and has urged retraction; and</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2-610_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>in either case suspend his own performance or proceed in accordance with the provisions of this article on the seller’s right to identify goods to the contract notwithstanding breach or to salvage unfinished goods (section 28:2-704).</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
